150 g Boursin Garlic and Fine Herbs Cheese
1 unit Red Onion
2 unit Shallot
170 g Green Beans
4 tbsp White Cooking Wine
20 g Gravy Spice Blend
14 g Parsley and Thyme
56 g Leek, sliced
2 unit Sandwich Bun
7.5 g Vegetable Stock Powder
1 tbsp Whole Grain Mustard
1.5 tbsp Butter*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450˚F. Wash and dry all produce.
In a small bowl, reserve 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) cooking wine. Set aside.
Peel, then thinly slice onion.
Peel, then thinly slice shallot.
Heat a large pot over medium heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) butter, then onions, leeks and shallots. Cook for 3-4 min, stirring occasionally, until onions soften slightly.
Add 1 tsp (2 tsp) sugar and season with salt and pepper. Cook for 4-6 min, stirring occasionally, until dark golden.

To pot with onions, add sprigs of thyme, remaining wine, vegetable stock powder, Gravy Spice Blend and 3 cups (6 cups) water.
Bring to a boil over high.
Once boiling, reduce heat to medium-low. Cook for 10-12 min, stirring occasionally, until onions are very soft.

Meanwhile, trim green beans.
Roughly chop parlsey.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
Add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) water and green beans. Cook for 5-6 min, stirring occasionally, until beans are tender.
Add reserved wine (from step 1), Dijon and half the parsley. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Remove from heat.

Meanwhile, halve buns.
Spread Boursin over top. Transfer to an unlined baking sheet.
Toast in the top of the oven for 3-6 min, until golden. (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn!)
Cut each Boursin toast in half. Set aside.

Remove and discard thyme stems from soup.
Divide soup between bowls, and then divide green beans and cheese toast between plates.
Sprinkle remaining parsley over top of soup.